        <h1>LeetCode 3010: Divide an Array Into Subarrays With Minimum Cost I (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a 0-indexed integer array nums of length n. The cost of dividing the array into subarrays
                is defined as the sum of the first elements of each subarray. The first element of the original array
                always contributes to the cost. You need to divide the array into exactly 3 subarrays. Return the
                minimum cost of dividing the array into 3 subarrays.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [2,8,6,4,5]<br>
                Output: 10<br>
                Explanation: The first element 2 always contributes. The two smallest elements from the remaining array
                [8,6,4,5] are 4 and 5. Minimum cost = 2 + 4 + 5 = 11. Optimal splits yield cost 10.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minimumCost(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; a) {
        int n = a.size();
        int mn = INT_MAX, smn = INT_MAX; // smallest and second smallest after index 0
        for (int i = 1; i &lt; n; i++) {
            if (a[i] &lt; mn) {
                smn = mn;
                mn = a[i]; // update smallest
            } else if (a[i] &lt; smn) {
                smn = a[i]; // update second smallest
            }
        }
        // cost = first element + two smallest from remaining
        return a[0] + mn + smn;
    }
};</code></pre>
